CatDescriptText: Obie Prince was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Out column published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1973, pg. 4, with question: "Do you think Black people will take advantage of the services offered by the Hill District Branch of the Bureau of Consumer Protection?" Answer reads: "I think its' a good thing for the community to have an office of this nature because we can get information about business dealings that we would not ordinarily know."
